CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 24, 1945, pg. 1 reads: "Attractive Mrs. Wyonella Croft, of 7346 Hermitage Street, a former North Carolina State College graduate, poses with one of the principal features of her first peace-time Thanksgiving Day's dinner since Pearl Harbor."
TitMainTitle: Wyonella Croft holding axe, posed with turkey in front of a market, street no. 2136
